    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Distinctive performers in Italian comedy, subsequently in French light comedy, and in English pantomime. The character has many attributes of the clown with the addition of mischievous intrigue; he usually wears particoloured bespangled tights and a visor, and carries a light ‘bat’ of lath as a magic wand.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
